
## Why This Exists
The existing `/api/version` endpoint performs a DB query to read `settings.update`, which can be costly for frequent health checks. The new `/api/heartbeat` endpoint offers a cheap alternative that confirms the service is up without any DB interaction.

## Implementation Notes
- Implemented in `pages/api/heartbeat.js`.
- Contains a clear comment stating that the route must remain DBâ€‘free.
- No imports from `lib/db/`, `lib/tools/`, or other heavy modules.
